FBIS4-32498 "dreeu123_d_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 SLOVAKIA KDH Names Electoral Leaders to 4 Constituencies KDH Names Electoral Leaders to 4 Constituencies AU2706114594 Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA in Slovak 24 Jun 94 p 2 AU2706114594 Bratislava NARODNA OBRODA Slovak BFN [Unattributed report in the "From Yesterday's Briefings" column: "Christian Democratic Movement--Electoral Leaders: Dzurinda, Pittner, Carnogursky"] [Text] The Christian Democratic Movement [KDH] leadership has approved the movement's election campaign. In east Slovakia, it will be led by [Minister of Transportation and Communications] Mikulas Dzurinda. Number two will be [KDH Deputy Chairman] Frantisek Miklosko. The number-one candidate in central Slovakia is [Interior Minister] Ladislav Pittner, number two is [Culture Minister] Lubo Roman. Number one in west Slovakia is [KDH Chairman] Jan Carnogursky, number two [Minister of Labor and Social Affairs] Julius Brocka. The election campaign in the Slovak capital, Bratislava, will be led by [Deputy Prime Minister] Ivan Simko.
